snippet.textDisplay: I am italian and would like to praise this song, it is just work of art. At first i could not understand who Nizamuddin and Khushrao were, i thought two lovers... I had to research... And to know that Khushrao wrotten this lyric, with such deep love for his maula is so touching. I have seen such  love still exists between friends in Pakistan, where two old men walk hand in hand or speak sweet words each others, here would seem so wrong. It is so sweet and i hope this will never end. This song has become my favourite, it moves my heart. And it is the first time for me listening to Abida ji. I could never imagine to sing 1% like her. Pakistani are so talented. As my husband once sang for me i said "you are so good", and he said no. But Pakistani have a gift in their mouth, also the ones who cannot sing sounds so good! I hope my son will learn to sing with the years, he loves pakistani songs too even if he is just 4. Such a blessing to have such singers to inspire us. Lot of love
